@page "/enigma-multiplayer"

<SeoHead Title="Enigma Co-op Operations | Shared Sessions and Expedition Sync"
         Description="Learn how Enigma co-op operations work, from invites and ready checks to synchronized room state, shared puzzle progress, and team completion."
         OpenGraphType="article"
         SchemaType="Article"
         Keywords="Enigma co-op command, shared expeditions, synchronized sectors, explorer team operations" />

<div class="content seo-page-shell">
    <section class="panel seo-page-hero">
        <div class="panel-heading">
            <div>
                <span class="profile-kicker">Co-op Operations</span>
                <h1>Enigma Co-op Command</h1>
            </div>
            <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/home">Back</a>
        </div>
        <p>Enigma co-op command is built for exactly two explorers per expedition, with shared room progression, synchronized puzzle state, and live session updates.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel seo-page-section">
        <h2>Operation Flow</h2>
        <h3>Create and Invite</h3>
        <p>The session owner starts a co-op lobby and invites a friend from their active friends list.</p>
        <h3>Join from Anywhere</h3>
        <p>Invites appear as live notifications and in the co-op lobby queue, so invited explorers can respond quickly without manual refresh.</p>
        <h3>Ready Check</h3>
        <p>Both explorers must be present and ready before entering the shared sector.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel seo-page-section">
        <h2>Shared Expedition Rules</h2>
        <h3>Synchronized Room State</h3>
        <p>Room transitions, puzzle completion, and major run events are synchronized at the session level.</p>
        <h3>Shared Objective Progress</h3>
        <p>Co-op puzzles and finish objectives are tracked for the team, not as separate solo attempts.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel seo-page-section">
        <h2>Completion and Failure</h2>
        <h3>Team Completion</h3>
        <p>A co-op expedition completes when both explorers satisfy the session finish conditions.</p>
        <h3>Session Abandonment</h3>
        <p>If an explorer leaves during an active co-op expedition, the session is marked abandoned and the expedition is recorded as a loss.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel seo-page-section">
        <h2>Live Co-op UX</h2>
        <h3>Status and Presence</h3>
        <p>Explorer online status, friend activity, and invite state are updated dynamically to reduce lobby friction.</p>
        <h3>Notification System</h3>
        <p>Invite arrivals, joins, and session state changes use the global app notification stream for fast feedback.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel seo-page-section">
        <h2>Continue Orientation</h2>
        <div class="seo-link-grid">
            <a class="seo-link-card" href="/about">
                <strong>Program Brief</strong>
                <span>How Enigma Corporation and A.R.D connect explorers, sectors, and governance.</span>
            </a>
            <a class="seo-link-card" href="/how-enigma-works">
                <strong>Operations Guide</strong>
                <span>Step-by-step expedition flow and how outcomes feed A.R.D systems.</span>
            </a>
            <a class="seo-link-card" href="/enigma-game-mechanics">
                <strong>System Mechanics</strong>
                <span>Room logic, puzzle mechanics, sector lifecycle, and progression rules.</span>
            </a>
        </div>
    </section>
</div>
